## Vercel Web Analytics Installation - Implementation Report

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the sutra-web project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart.

### Changes Made

1. **Package Installation**
   - Installed `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1
   - Updated package.json to include the new dependency
   - Updated package-lock.json with the full dependency tree

2. **Code Integration**
   - Modified `src/app/layout.tsx` to import and include the Analytics component
   - Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next"`
   - Added `<Analytics />` component inside the body element, following Next.js App Router best practices

### Framework Context

This project uses:
- **Next.js 16.2.3** with the **App Router** pattern
- The Analytics component was added to the root layout file (`src/app/layout.tsx`)
- This follows the recommended approach for Next.js App Router as specified in the Vercel documentation

### Verification Steps Completed

✅ **Build Test**: Successfully ran `npm run build` - project compiles without errors
✅ **Linting**: Ran `npm run lint` on layout.tsx - no new errors introduced
✅ **Dependencies**: Verified package.json and package-lock.json are properly updated
✅ **Code Quality**: Preserved existing code structure and formatting

### Implementation Details

The Analytics component was placed at the end of the body element, after the children content, which is the recommended placement according to Vercel's documentation. This ensures:
- Analytics tracking initializes after page content loads
- No impact on initial page render performance
- Proper tracking of page views and user interactions

### Next Steps for User

To complete the setup:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Project Settings → Analytics)
3. After deployment, analytics will automatically start tracking:
   - Page views
   - User sessions
   - Geographic data
   - Device and browser information
4. Verify by checking the browser's Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/*`

### Files Modified

- `sutra-web/package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `sutra-web/package-lock.json` - Updated with new dependencies
- `sutra-web/src/app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics component import and usage

All changes follow the official Vercel documentation and Next.js best practices.
